name: Ramen
description: A noodle soup from Japan, flavored with soy sauce or miso, with toppings like sliced pork, nori, and green onions.

name: Steak
description: A cut of meat, typically beef, grilled or pan-fried. Varieties include ribeye, T-bone, and sirloin.

name: Sandwich
description: Consists of vegetables, sliced cheese or meat, placed between slices of bread, served cold or hot.

name: Hamburger
description: A sandwich consisting of one or more cooked patties of ground meat, usually beef, placed inside a sliced bread roll or bun.

name: Pizza
description: A dish of Italian origin consisting of a flat, round base of dough baked with a topping of tomato sauce and cheese, often with added meat or vegetables.

name: Tendon
description: A Japanese dish consisting of a bowl of rice topped with tempura (battered and fried seafood or vegetables).

name: Noodles
description: A staple in many cultures, made from unleavened dough which is stretched, extruded, or rolled flat and cut into various shapes.

name: Sushi
description: A Japanese dish of prepared vinegared rice, accompanied by various ingredients such as seafood, often raw, and vegetables.
